sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as Sales Rep<br/>(screen flow user)
    participant F as Screen Flow<br/>Travel Desk
    participant N as Named Credential<br/>Engine
    participant T as Amadeus Token Endpoint<br/>/v1/security/oauth2/token
    participant A as Amadeus City Search<br/>/v1/reference-data/locations/cities

    U->>F: Types the client's HQ city: "PAR"
    F->>N: HTTP Callout action —<br/>GET callout:Amadeus/…?keyword=PAR&max=1
    Note over N,T: Real OAuth — handled invisibly
    N->>T: POST grant_type=client_credentials<br/>(API Key + Secret from the Principal)
    T-->>N: access_token (lives ~30 min, cached)
    N->>A: GET …?keyword=PAR&max=1<br/>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;
    A-->>N: { "data": [ { "name": "PARIS", "iataCode": "PAR",<br/>"geoCode": { "latitude": …, "longitude": … } } ] }
    N-->>F: 200 OK — a typed collection
    F->>F: Loop = the JSON parser →<br/>CityName, CityCode, Lat, Lon
    F-->>U: "PARIS (PAR) — save to this Account?" → Update Records

    Note over U,A: The flow never sees a token or a secret —<br/>Modules 1–4 built the machine that makes this boring
